0. Explanation on lower bound and upper bound a.k.s ilower,iupper, and so on.

   Example: If the number of ghost cell is 3, then

    ilower=-2                                              iupper=il+3
       |                                                      |
    ___|______________________________________________________|__
   |   | |     |     ||     |     |     |     ||     |     |  |  |
   |  -2 |  -1 |  0  ||  1  |  2  | ... |  il || il+1| il+2| il+3|  <--- cell number
   |_____|_____|_____||_____|_____|_____|_____||_____|_____|_____|
  -2    -1     0      1     2     3    il    il+1  il+2  il+3  il+4 <--- grid number
   |_________________|                        |_________________|
            |                                          |
    ghost cell layers                          ghost cell layers
  
	In some subroutines, ilower is ilow and iupper is iupp.     
